for deadeye p2 doesnt float--it's DD/BB no? and i think lancetooth really depends; sometimes nat counduit into tooth is really good (although games with lance are almost always bullshit for one side or the other)
for things like flameanumis p2 only floats 2 (DD/DB). Im not super familiar with drake lines but I've found that dd/ddc/ddb/(urban + forge) or some varient usually works well enough depending on random set
I agree that p2 doesnt really have a set in stone forge line though; but I'm not sure if this is really a bad thing
